<subSubSection id="B21D93C8375C7E76E43C9FF54818E05A" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnostic features">
<paragraph id="334F8D9FCBFF9EDEDC2C5BCCDE0D9ECD" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnostic features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A02516B2C774DC9A41AB1C025F067BE4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Dark brown tegmina with distinct dots (Fig. 1a, b, c). Pronotum has one pointed tooth on anterior side and several on posterior end; in the centre two transverse sulci are located just behind the middle (Fig. 1
<normalizedToken id="34D64EAC2321A23D6F3B9663AF64DADB" originalValue="a–d">a-d</normalizedToken>
). Centre of fore, mid, and hind femur with rounded dots on its lower side. Tegmina slightly shorter than wings. Ovipositor with small teeth on its apex (Fig. 1e).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
